A knife-wielding woman allegedly attempted to attack another woman at the Jetline.com printing company in Fourways on Cedar Road. The incident was captured on a video footage on Monday, Fourways Review reported. It is alleged the woman ran into Jetline.com, situated next to the FNB, with a large knife. She was there to attack another woman she believed was having relations with her husband. She entered the premises with an accomplice who was carrying a baby. The attacker, however, was restrained by staff of the print shop. Noticeably angry and upset, she was escorted by Fidelity Security guards, placed inside their van and taken to Fourways Mall s main security office. No injuries were sustained. &#8211; Caxton News Service For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.